Step 1: LC reference (alpha=0)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  Analytical: V_eff_LC(T3,MX) = (16*pi^4/kappa^2) * r * [V^2*r^2/3 + 2*V*eta*r*theta + 3*eta^2]
  => no finite minimum: dV/deta=0 at eta=0, dV/dr=0 needs V=0 => trivial only

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 2: Analytic MX stationary conditions on the theta_NY=0 slice
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  From dV/deta = dV/dV = 0 at theta_NY = 0:
    V* = ±3*sqrt(1/alpha)/4
    eta* = ±r*sqrt(1/alpha)/4
  Therefore alpha < 0 gives purely imaginary stationary points.
  => no finite real MX critical point exists on the alpha<0 branch

